Abies nebrodensis.label: Abies nebrodensis
Abies nebrodensis.description: Sicilian Fir is a fir native to the Nebrodi and Madonie mountains in northern Sicily. It is a medium-size evergreen coniferous tree growing to 15–25 m tall and with a trunk diameter of up to 1 m. It occurs at altitudes of 1400-1,600 m. Wikipedia

Açaí palm.label: Açaí palm
Açaí palm.description: The açaí palm is a species of palm tree in the genus Euterpe cultivated for its fruit and superior hearts of palm. Its name comes from the Portuguese adaptation of the Tupian word ïwaca'i, '[fruit that] cries or expels water'. Wikipedia

Abies nordmanniana.label: Abies nordmanniana
Abies nordmanniana.description: Abies nordmanniana, the Nordmann Fir, is a fir native to the mountains west and east of the Black Sea, in Turkey, Georgia, Russian Caucasus and northern parts of Armenia. Wikipedia

Acacia karroo.label: Vachellia karroo
Acacia karroo.description:
Vachellia karroo also known as the Sweet Thorn, is a species of Vachellia, native to southern Africa from southern Angola east to Mozambique, and south to South Africa.
It is a shrub or small to medium-sized tree which grows to height of 12m. Wikipedia

Acacia mellifera.label: Senegalia mellifera
Acacia mellifera.description: Senegalia mellifera is a common thorn tree in Africa. The name mellifera refers to its sweet-smelling blossoms and honey. Its lumber turns pitch black when oiled. Common names of the tree include Blackthorn and Swarthaak. Wikipedia

Acer buergerianum.label: Acer buergerianum
Acer buergerianum.description: Acer buergerianum is a species of maple native to eastern China and Taiwan. Wikipedia

Acer carpinifolium.label: Acer carpinifolium
Acer carpinifolium.description: Acer carpinifolium is a species of maple native to Japan, on the islands of Honshū, Kyūshū, and Shikoku, where it grows in woodlands and alongside streams in mountainous areas. Wikipedia

Acer palmatum.label: Acer palmatum
Acer palmatum.description: Acer palmatum, called Japanese Maple or Smooth Japanese Maple is a species of woody plant native to Japan, North Korea, South Korea, China, eastern Mongolia, and southeast Russia. Wikipedia

Acer tegmentosum.label: Acer tegmentosum
Acer tegmentosum.description: Acer tegmentosum, Manchurian striped maple is a species of maple genus, which is natively found in the south of the Russian Far East, North-Eastern China and in Korea. Wikipedia

Acrotriche.label: Acrotriche
Acrotriche.description:
Acrotriche is a genus of flowering plants in the family Ericaceae. Species occur in all states of Australia. They include
Acrotriche affinis DC. - Ridged Ground-berry
Acrotriche aggregata R.Br. Wikipedia

Aconitum lycoctonum.label: Aconitum lycoctonum
Aconitum lycoctonum.description:
Aconitum lycoctonum is a species of flowering plant in the genus Aconitum, of the family Ranunculaceae, native to Europe and northern Asia.
Lycoctonum is a rendering in modern Latin of the traditional name "wolf's bane". Wikipedia

Adonis aestivalis.label: Adonis aestivalis
Adonis aestivalis.description: Adonis aestivalis is a medicinal and ornamental plant. It is native to Europe but has been introduced elsewhere, such as the western and eastern parts of the United States. Wikipedia

Aciphylla.label: Aciphylla
Aciphylla.description: Aciphylla is a genus of about 40 species of plants in the Apiaceae family, endemic to New Zealand and Australia. They generally grow as tall spikes surrounded by rosettes of stiff, pointed leaves. Some species are known as Spaniard Grass. Wikipedia

Aegopodium podagraria.label: Ground Elder
Aegopodium podagraria.description: Aegopodium podagraria L. commonly called ground elder, herb gerard, bishop's weed, goutweed, and snow-in-the-mountain, is a perennial plant in the carrot family that grows in shady places. Wikipedia

Aeschynomene.label: Aeschynomene
Aeschynomene.description: Aeschynomene is a genus of flowering plants in the family Fabaceae, and was recently assigned to the informal monophyletic Dalbergia clade of the Dalbergieae. They are known commonly as jointvetches. Wikipedia

Aesculus flava.label: Aesculus flava
Aesculus flava.description: Aesculus flava, the yellow buckeye, common buckeye, or sweet buckeye, is a species of deciduous tree. It is native to the Ohio Valley and Appalachian Mountains of the Eastern United States. Wikipedia

Aesculus pavia.label: Aesculus pavia
Aesculus pavia.description: Aesculus pavia, known as Red Buckeye or Firecracker Plant, is a species of deciduous flowering plant. Wikipedia

Aethionema.label: Aethionema
Aethionema.description: Aethionema syn. Eunomia is a genus of flowering plants, within the family Brassicaceae, subfamily Brassicoideae. The genus is collectively known as the stonecresses. Wikipedia

Afrocarpus.label: Afrocarpus
Afrocarpus.description: Afrocarpus is a genus of conifers belonging to the podocarp family Podocarpaceae. Afrocarpus was designated a genus in 1989, when several species formerly classified in Podocarpus and Nageia were reclassified. Two to six species are recognized. Wikipedia

Agathis australis.label: Agathis australis
Agathis australis.description: Agathis australis, commonly known by its Māori name kauri, is a coniferous tree of Araucariaceae in the genus Agathis, found north of 38°S in the northern districts of New Zealand's North Island. Wikipedia

Aglaonema.label: Aglaonema
Aglaonema.description: Aglaonema is a genus of flowering plants in the arum family, Araceae. They are native to tropical and subtropical regions of Asia. They are known commonly as Chinese evergreens. Wikipedia

Aglianico.label: Aglianico
Aglianico.description: Aglianico is a black grape grown in the Basilicata and Campania regions of Italy. The vine originated in Greece and was brought to the south of Italy by Greek settlers. The name may be a corruption of vitis hellenica, Latin for "Greek vine." Wikipedia

Ailanthus.label: Ailanthus
Ailanthus.description: Ailanthus is a genus of trees belonging to the family Simaroubaceae, in the order Sapindales. The genus is native from east Asia south to northern Australasia. Wikipedia

Agrostemma.label: Agrostemma
Agrostemma.description: Agrostemma is a genus of annual plants in the Caryophyllaceae family, containing the species known as corncockles. Its best-known member is A. githago, the Common Corncockle, which is a native of Europe where it is simply called "the Corncockle". Wikipedia

Agrostis capillaris.label: Agrostis capillaris
Agrostis capillaris.description: Agrostis capillaris is a rhizomatous and stoloniferous perennial in the grass family. It is native to Eurasia and has been widely introduced in many parts of the world. Wikipedia

Aichryson.label: Aichryson
Aichryson.description:
Aichryson is a genus of about 15 species of succulent, subtropical plants, mostly native to the Canary Islands, with a few in the Azores, Madeira and Morocco, and one in Portugal.
The species of Aichryson are not frost-resistant. Wikipedia

Agrostis stolonifera.label: Agrostis stolonifera
Agrostis stolonifera.description: Agrostis stolonifera is a perennial grass species in the Poaceae family. Wikipedia

Albana (grape).label: Albana
Albana (grape).description:
Albana is a white Italian wine grape planted primarily in the Emilia-Romagna region.
The wine made from the grape, Albana di Romagna, was first awarded DOCG status in 1987. Wikipedia

Aldrovanda.label: Aldrovanda
Aldrovanda.description: Aldrovanda is a genus of carnivorous plants encompassing one extant species and numerous extinct taxa. Wikipedia

Allamanda.label: Allamanda
Allamanda.description: Allamanda is a genus of flowering plants in the dogbane family, Apocynaceae. They are native to the Americas, where they are distributed from Mexico to Argentina. Wikipedia

Aleurites.label: Aleurites
Aleurites.description: Aleurites is a small arborescent genus of flowering plants in the tropical and subtropical regions of Asia, the Pacific and South America, belonging to the spurge family Euphorbiaceae. Wikipedia

Allamanda cathartica.label: Allamanda cathartica
Allamanda cathartica.description: Allamanda cathartica is a species of flowering plant of the genus Allamanda in the family Apocynaceae. It is native to Brazil. This plant is cited in Flora Brasiliensis by Carl Friedrich Philipp von Martius. Wikipedia

Allotropa.label: Allotropa
Allotropa.description: Allotropa virgata is in the family Ericaceae and is the only species of the genus Allotropa. It is a perennial plant that gets its common names from the distinct white and red or maroon stripes along its erect peduncle. Wikipedia

Amelanchier alnifolia.label: Saskatoon
Amelanchier alnifolia.description: Amelanchier alnifolia, the saskatoon, Pacific serviceberry, western serviceberry, alder-leaf shadbush, dwarf shadbush, chuckley pear, or western juneberry, is a shrub with edible berry-like fruit, native ... Wikipedia

Ampelopsis.label: Ampelopsis
Ampelopsis.description: Ampelopsis is a genus of climbing shrubs, in the grape family Vitaceae. The name is derived from the Greek word ampelos, which means "vine". The genus was named in 1803. Wikipedia

Anacyclus clavatus.label: Anacyclus clavatus
Anacyclus clavatus.description: Anacyclus clavata also known as Camomilla tomentosa, Pusteni targok, Vit bertram, White Anacyclus and White Buttons is a member of the genus Anacyclus and the tribe Anthemideae and family Asteraceae. Wikipedia

Anabasis (plant).label: Anabasis
Anabasis (plant).description: Anabasis is a genus of the subfamily Salsoloideae in the family Amaranthaceae. It is distributed in southern Europe, North Africa, and Asia. Wikipedia

Anagallis.label: Anagallis
Anagallis.description: Anagallis is a genus of about 20–25 species of flowering plants in the family Myrsinaceae, commonly called pimpernel and perhaps best known for the scarlet pimpernel referred to in literature. Wikipedia

Ananas bracteatus.label: Ananas bracteatus
Ananas bracteatus.description: Ananas bracteatus is a species of the pineapple. They are grown as ornamental plants for their decorative red fruit. They can be used as hedges for home security. In colder places they can be grown indoors as a houseplant. Wikipedia

Ananas fritzmuelleri.label: Ananas fritzmuelleri
Ananas fritzmuelleri.description: Ananas fritzmuelleri is a species of the genus Ananas. This species is endemic to Brazil. Wikipedia

Anastatica.label: Anastatica
Anastatica.description: Anastatica is a monotypic genus with the type species Anastatica hierochuntica. The genus is a member of the family Brassicaceae, in the division Magnoliophyta of the class Magnoliopsida. Wikipedia

Ancellotta.label: Ancellotta
Ancellotta.description: Ancellotta is a wine grape variety mainly grown in the Emilia-Romagna region of Italy, but also in some other parts of north Italy, and in south Switzerland. Wikipedia

Anchusa arvensis.label: Anchusa arvensis
Anchusa arvensis.description: Anchusa arvensis is a plant species of the genus Anchusa. Its common names include small bugloss and annual bugloss. This is a hairy annual herb which may reach one half to one meter in height. Wikipedia

Andrachne.label: Andrachne
Andrachne.description: Andrachne is a genus of flowering plants in the family Phyllanthaceae. It is one of eight genera in the tribe Poranthereae. Andrachne comprises 22 species. Wikipedia

Anemone nemorosa.label: Anemone nemorosa
Anemone nemorosa.description: Anemone nemorosa is an early-spring flowering plant in the genus Anemone in the family Ranunculaceae, native to Europe. Common names include wood anemone, windflower, thimbleweed, and smell fox, an allusion to the musky smell of the leaves. Wikipedia

Andromeda polifolia.label: Andromeda polifolia
Andromeda polifolia.description: Andromeda polifolia, common name bog rosemary, is a species of flowering plant native to northern parts of the Northern Hemisphere. It is the only member of the genus Andromeda, and is only found in bogs in cold peat-accumulating areas. Wikipedia

Akaniaceae.label: Akaniaceae
Akaniaceae.description: Akaniaceae is a family of flowering plants in the order Brassicales. It comprises two monotypic genera of trees, Akania and Bretschneidera native to southern East China, Vietnam, Taiwan, and eastern Australia. Wikipedia

Anemone trifolia.label: Anemone trifolia
Anemone trifolia.description: Anemone trifolia is a perennial herbaceous plant in the genus Anemone. Wikipedia

Annonaceae.label: Annonaceae
Annonaceae.description: Annonaceae, the custard apple family, is a family of flowering plants consisting of trees, shrubs, or rarely lianas. With about 2300 to 2500 species and more than 130 genera, it is the largest family in Magnoliales. Wikipedia

Annona glabra.label: Annona glabra
Annona glabra.description: Annona glabra is a tropical fruit tree in the family Annonaceae, in the same genus as the Soursop and Cherimoya. Common names include Pond-apple, Alligator-apple Swamp apple, Corkwood, Bobwood, and Monkey-apple. Wikipedia

Anthurium.label: Anthurium
Anthurium.description: Anthurium, is a genus of about 1000 species of flowering plants, the largest genus of the arum family, Araceae. General common names include anthurium, tailflower, flamingo flower, and laceleaf. Wikipedia

Araucaria araucana.label: Monkey puzzle tree
Araucaria araucana.description: Araucaria araucana is an evergreen tree growing to 40 m tall with a 2-m trunk diameter. The tree is native to central and southern Chile and western Argentina. Araucaria araucana is the hardiest species in the conifer genus Araucaria. Wikipedia

Araucaria.label: Araucaria
Araucaria.description: Araucaria is a genus of evergreen coniferous trees in the family Araucariaceae. There are 19 extant species in the genus, with a Gondwanan natural distribution in New Caledonia, Norfolk Island, eastern ... Wikipedia

Arctium tomentosum.label: Arctium tomentosum
Arctium tomentosum.description: Arctium tomentosum, commonly known as the downy burdock or woolly burdock, is a species of burdock that grows in Europe and western Asia. It is a biennial herbaceous plant. It was described by Philip Miller in 1768. Wikipedia

Argentina anserina.label: Silverweed Cinquefoil
Argentina anserina.description: Argentina anserina, also known as common silverweed, silverweed cinquefoil or just "silverweed", is a flowering perennial plant in the rose family Rosaceae. Wikipedia

Ariocarpus.label: Ariocarpus
Ariocarpus.description:
Ariocarpus is a genus of 8 species of succulent, subtropical plants of the Cactaceae family.
The name comes from the ancient Greek "aria" and "carpos" because of the resemblance of the fruit of the two genus in acorn form. Wikipedia

Aristotelia chilensis.label: Aristotelia chilensis
Aristotelia chilensis.description: Aristotelia chilensis is a species of the Elaeocarpaceae family native to the Valdivian temperate rainforests of Chile and adjacent regions of southern Argentina. Maqui is sparsely cultivated. Wikipedia

Armenian cucumber.label: Armenian cucumber
Armenian cucumber.description: The Armenian cucumber, Cucumis melo var. flexuosus, is a type of long, slender fruit which tastes like a cucumber and looks somewhat like a cucumber inside. It is actually a variety of muskmelon, a species closely related to the cucumber. Wikipedia

Arnicastrum guerrerense.label: Arnicastrum guerrerense
Arnicastrum guerrerense.description: Arnicastrum guerrerense Villaseñor 1986 from the family Asteraceae is a perennial herb with yellow flowers known from Mexico. Wikipedia

Arracacha.label: Arracacia xanthorrhiza
Arracacha.description: Arracacia xanthorrhiza is a root vegetable originally from the Andes, somewhat intermediate between the carrot and celery. Its starchy taproot is a popular food item in South America where it is a major commercial crop. Wikipedia

Arrojadoa.label: Arrojadoa
Arrojadoa.description: Arrojadoa is a genus of cacti, comprising 6 species and several varieties. It is named after the Brazilian Miguel Arrojado Lisboa. The genus occurs only in northern Brazil and is found at rocky places, under shrubs, which support their frail stalk. Wikipedia

Artemisia cina.label: Artemisia cina
Artemisia cina.description: Artemisia cina, commonly known as santonica, Levant wormseed, and wormseed, is an herbaceous perennial of the daisy family. Its dried flowerheads are the source of the vermifugic drug santonin since ancient times. Wikipedia

Artemisia frigida.label: Artemisia frigida
Artemisia frigida.description: Artemisia frigida is a species of flowering plant in the aster family known by the common names fringed sagebrush, prairie sagewort, arctic sage and pasture sage. Wikipedia

Artemisia herba-alba.label: Artemisia herba-alba
Artemisia herba-alba.description: Artemisia herba-alba, also known as white wormwood, is a perennial shrub in the genus Artemisia that grows commonly on the steppes of the Mediterranean regions in Northern Africa, Western Asia and ... Wikipedia

Artemisia tridentata.label: Artemisia tridentata
Artemisia tridentata.description: Artemisia tridentata, commonly called "big sagebrush" or "sagebrush", is an aromatic shrub from the family Asteraceae, which grows in arid and semi-arid conditions, throughout a range of cold desert, ... Wikipedia

Asafoetida.label: Asafoetida
Asafoetida.description: Asafoetida, انگدان, آنغوزه or asafetida, is the dried latex exuded from the rhizome or tap root of several species of Ferula, a perennial herb that grows 1 to 1.5 m tall. Wikipedia

Asplenium ruta-muraria.label: Asplenium ruta-muraria
Asplenium ruta-muraria.description: Asplenium ruta-muraria is a species of fern commonly known as wall-rue. In Germany, it is known as Mauerraute or Mauerstreifenfarn. It is a very small epipetric species, growing exclusively on limestone and other calcareous rocks. Wikipedia

Asimina triloba.label: Asimina triloba
Asimina triloba.description: Asimina triloba, the pawpaw, paw paw, paw-paw, or common pawpaw, is a species of Asimina in the same plant family as the custard-apple, cherimoya, sweetsop, ylang-ylang and soursop. Wikipedia

Aspalathus.label: Aspalathus
Aspalathus.description: Aspalathus is a genus of flowering plants in the legume family, Fabaceae. The yellow flowers and spiny habit of some species have suggested a resemblance to Ulex europaeus, the thorny "English gorse" ... Wikipedia

Asplenium trichomanes.label: Asplenium trichomanes
Asplenium trichomanes.description: Asplenium trichomanes is a small fern in the spleenwort genus Asplenium. It is a widespread and common species, occurring almost worldwide in a variety of rocky habitats. It is a variable fern with several subspecies. Wikipedia

Aster tripolium.label: Aster tripolium
Aster tripolium.description: The Sea Aster is a plant of northern Europe that is confined in its distribution to salt marshes, estuaries and occasionally to inland salt works. Wikipedia

Asteridae.label: Asteridae
Asteridae.description: Asteridae is an obsolete botanical name at the rank of subclass. Composition of the subclass has also varied, however, by definition it always includes the family Asteraceae. Wikipedia

Astragalus cicer.label: Astragalus cicer
Astragalus cicer.description: Cicer milkvetch is a perennial flowering plant native to Eastern Europe, popularized and subsequently transported to areas in Southern Europe, North America, and South America. Wikipedia

Astrantia.label: Astrantia
Astrantia.description: Astrantia is a genus of herbaceous plants in the family Apiaceae, endemic to Central, Eastern and Southern Europe and the Caucasus.The Genus name comes from the Greek word for star in reference to the star-like quality of the flower heads. Wikipedia

Astrantia major.label: Astrantia major
Astrantia major.description: Astrantia major, common name great masterwort, is a species of flowering plant in the family Apiaceae, native to central and eastern Europe. Growing to 90 cm tall by 45 cm broad, it is an herbaceous perennial, much used in gardens. Wikipedia

Astroloma.label: Astroloma
Astroloma.description: Astroloma is an endemic Australian genus of around 20 species of flowering plants in the family Ericaceae. Wikipedia

Atractylis.label: Atractylis
Atractylis.description:
The Distaff thistle is a plant of the genus Atractylis in the daisy family.
In the Greek island of Crete the species Atractylis gummifera, which is called by the locals kollies, akolletes, sakizi, ... Wikipedia

Athrotaxis.label: Athrotaxis
Athrotaxis.description: Athrotaxis is a genus of two to three species of conifers in the cypress family, Cupressaceae. The genus is endemic to western Tasmania, where they grow in high altitude temperate rainforests. Wikipedia

Athyrium filix-femina.label: Athyrium filix-femina
Athyrium filix-femina.description: Athyrium filix-femina is a large, feathery species of fern native throughout most of the temperate Northern Hemisphere, where it is often abundant in damp, shady woodland environments and is often grown for decoration. Wikipedia

Avena nuda.label: Avena nuda
Avena nuda.description:
Avena nuda is a species of grass with edible seeds.
Avena nuda was grown in Cornwall in the 18th century. Pilez was used as a substitute for oatmeal and for fattening calves.
When threshed, the hull separates quite readily from the grain. Wikipedia

Atraphaxis.label: Atraphaxis
Atraphaxis.description: Atraphaxis is a genus of plants in the family Polygonaceae with about 18 species. Wikipedia

Baco Blanc.label: Baco blanc
Baco Blanc.description: Baco blanc or Baco 22A is a French-American hybrid grape variety. It is a cross of Folle blanche and the Noah grape, created in the 1898 by the grape breeder François Baco. Folle blanche is its Vitis vinifera parent. Wikipedia

Banksia spinulosa.label: Banksia spinulosa
Banksia spinulosa.description: The Hairpin Banksia is a species of woody shrub, of the genus Banksia in the Proteaceae family, native to eastern Australia. Wikipedia

Banksia grandis.label: Banksia grandis
Banksia grandis.description: Banksia grandis, commonly known as Bull Banksia, Giant Banksia or Mangite, is a common and distinctive tree in South West Western Australia. Wikipedia

Azuki bean.label: Azuki bean
Azuki bean.description: The azuki bean, also known as adzuki or aduki, is an annual vine, Vigna angularis, widely grown throughout East Asia and the Himalayas for its small bean. The cultivars most familiar in Northeast Asia have a uniform red color. Wikipedia

Berchemia.label: Berchemia
Berchemia.description: Berchemia is a genus of plants in the family Rhamnaceae, named after Dutch botanist Berthout van Berchem. They are climbing plants or small to medium-sized trees that occur in Africa, Asia and the Americas. Wikipedia

Bennettitales.label: Bennettitales
Bennettitales.description: Bennettitales is an extinct order of seed plants that first appeared in the Triassic period and became extinct in most areas toward the end of the Cretaceous, although some Bennettitales appear to have ... Wikipedia

Biophytum.label: Biophytum
Biophytum.description: Biophytum is a genus of about 50 species of annual and perennial herbaceous plants in the family Oxalidaceae. It is found in tropical and subtropical areas worldwide. The annual Biophytum sensitivum is a traditional medicine in Nepal. Wikipedia

Black Muscat.label: Black Muscat
Black Muscat.description: Black Muscat is a Vitis vinifera grape variety derived from the crossing of the Schiava Grossa and Muscat of Alexandria varieties. Wikipedia
